    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="892"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d892">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Marquis of Tweeddale, president Hongkong and Manila Telegraph, informs me
                    that they hold their concessions from Spanish Government on condition that they
                    shall not send telegrams when forbidden by Spain. This formal order has been
                    given by Spain. They are, therefore, compelled to cease working for the present.
                    He professed friendly feelings and desire that we should establish ourselves
                    permanently in Philippine Islands, but declared inability to act otherwise in
                    view of his concessions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
